{
  "title": "Errors",
  "href": "http://www.google.com/design/spec/patterns/errors.html",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "intro",
      "html": "<p>Errors occur when an app fails to complete what is expected, such as:</p><ul><li>The app does not understand user input</li><li>The system or app fails</li><li>A user intends to run incompatible operations concurrently</li></ul><p>Minimize errors by designing apps that make it easy for users to input information flexibly. Apps should accept common data formats that use affordances to improve user understanding. </p><p>How to address errors:</p><ul><li>Clearly communicate what is happening</li><li>Describe how a user can resolve it</li><li>Preserve as much user-entered input as possible</li></ul>"
    },
    {
      "type": "article-list",
      "articles": [
        {
          "type": "article",
          "title": "User input errors",
          "modules": [
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p>Help users fix input errors as soon as they are detected. Disable the submission of a form if errors are detected, and if detected only after form submission, clearly explain the error and how to fix it.</p>"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "module",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "module-body",
                  "html": "<p><strong>Helper text</strong>&#xA0;may be included before, during, or after a user interacts with each field on a form. </p><p>Show <strong>error text</strong>&#xA0;only after user interaction with a field. If the user inputs incorrect data, helper text may transform into error text. </p><p>Minimize form text to the essentials. Not every text field needs helper and/or error text. </p><p>Specification:</p><p>Place 16dp of vertical space between text fields and the below error text. </p>"
                },
                {
                  "type": "figure-group",
                  "figures": [
                    {
                      "type": "figure",
                      "mediaType": "image",
